	<div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">
	</div>
	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Badb</h1>
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For hacker, see <a href="/wiki/Vladislav_Horohorin" title="Vladislav Horohorin">Vladislav Horohorin</a>.</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg/250px-Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="224" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg/375px-Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg/500px-Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1223" data-file-height="1094" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Corvus_cornix_-perching-8.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Badb would commonly take the form of the <a href="/wiki/Hooded_crow" title="Hooded crow">hooded crow</a>.</div></div></div>
<p>In <a href="/wiki/Irish_mythology" title="Irish mythology">Irish mythology</a>, the <b>Badb</b> (<a href="/wiki/Old_Irish" title="Old Irish">Old Irish</a>, <small>pronounced&#160;</small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA" title="Help:IPA">[ˈbaðβ]</a></span>), or in <a href="/wiki/Irish_language" title="Irish language">Modern Irish</a> <b>Badhbh</b> (<small>Irish pronunciation:&#160;</small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Irish" title="Help:IPA/Irish">[ˈba̠u]</a></span>, <small><a href="/wiki/Munster_Irish" title="Munster Irish">Munster Irish</a>:&#160;</small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/Irish" title="Help:IPA/Irish">[ˈba̠iv]</a></span>)—also meaning "<a href="/wiki/Crow" title="Crow">crow</a>"—is a <a href="/wiki/War_goddess" class="mw-redirect" title="War goddess">war goddess</a> who takes the form of a crow, and is thus sometimes known as <b>Badb Catha</b> ("battle crow").<sup id="cite_ref-eDILbadb_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-eDILbadb-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> She is known to cause fear and confusion among soldiers to move the tide of battle to her favoured side. Badb may also appear prior to a battle to foreshadow the extent of the carnage to come, or to predict the death of a notable person.  She would sometimes do this through wailing cries, leading to comparisons with the <a href="/wiki/Banshee" title="Banshee">bean-sídhe</a> (banshee).
</p><p>With her sisters, <a href="/wiki/Macha_(Irish_mythology)" class="mw-redirect" title="Macha (Irish mythology)">Macha</a> and the Morrigan or <a href="/wiki/Morr%C3%ADgan" class="mw-redirect" title="Morrígan"> Anand</a>, Badb is part of a <a href="/wiki/Triple_deity" title="Triple deity">trio</a> of war goddesses known as <i><a href="/wiki/The_Morr%C3%ADgan" title="The Morrígan">the three Morrígna</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-Invasions_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Invasions-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-CMT166-CELT_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CMT166-CELT-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-CMT167_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CMT167-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
